Get the Digital Elevation Model (DEM) tile url sources

Source: R/mpc_srcs.R
mpc_dtm_src.Rd

Get the Digital Elevation Model (DEM) tile url sources from the Microsoft Planetary Computer STAC catalogue.

Usage

mpc_dtm_src(
  aoi,
  collection = c("cop-dem-glo-30", "cop-dem-glo-90", "alos-dem", "nasadem"),
  vsicurl = TRUE,
  sign_items = TRUE,
  subscription_key = Sys.getenv("rsi_pc_key")
)

Arguments

aoi

a spatial extent which can be provided as a numeric bounding box or using a spatial object from either the terra, sf or stars packages.

collection

A character. one of: "cop-dem-glo-30", "cop-dem-glo-90", "alos-dem", "nasadem".

vsicurl

logical with default TRUE. If TRUE the '/vsicurl/' prefix is appended to returned urls which increases read speed for gdal. see https://gdal.org/user/virtual_file_systems.html#vsicurl-http-https-ftp-files-random-access for more information.

sign_items

logical with default TRUE. If TRUE the STAC items are signed this is now required for the planetary computer API.

subscription_key

A character. The subscription key for the planetary computer API. This can be set as an environment variable 'rsi_pc_key' ( the default for the rsi package) or 'MPC_TOKEN' (the default for the sits package). It isn't essential to set this token but it should improve the performance of the API. See sign_planetary_computer

Value

A character vector of url paths.
